Come on. John.

383
00:44:56.000 --> 00:44:56.955
No.

384
00:44:59.320 --> 00:45:00.275
Why not?

385
00:45:00.680 --> 00:45:02.796
I want you to meet my fr...

386
00:45:05.800 --> 00:45:07.756
Don't you want to meet my friends?

387
00:45:08.160 --> 00:45:12.073
I don't want to meet anybody.
I really don't want to meet anybody.

388
00:45:12.800 --> 00:45:14.392
I just want to be with you.

389
00:45:21.680 --> 00:45:22.999
I'll start the dishes.

390
00:45:23.360 --> 00:45:24.588
Let me tell you something.

391
00:45:25.880 --> 00:45:26.915
You don't do dishes.

392
00:45:27.600 --> 00:45:30.194
You don't ever have to do dishes.
I'll do the dishes.

393
00:45:32.960 --> 00:45:34.757
And I'll buy the groceries.

394
00:45:35.880 --> 00:45:37.393
And I'll cook the food.

395
00:45:40.960 --> 00:45:41.995
And I'll feed you.

396
00:45:43.000 --> 00:45:44.956
And I'll dress you in the morning.

397
00:45:46.280 --> 00:45:48.396
And I'll undress you at night.

398
00:45:49.400 --> 00:45:50.958
And I'll bathe you.

399
00:45:52.920 --> 00:45:54.797
And I'll take care of you.

400
00:45:58.000 --> 00:46:02.118
And you can see your friends in the
daytime. I just want the nighttime...

401
00:46:02.520 --> 00:46:03.873
...from now on to be...

402
00:46:04.440 --> 00:46:05.395
...ours.

403
00:46:19.320 --> 00:46:20.594
Yes?

404
00:46:23.360 --> 00:46:24.588
Okay. fine.

405
00:46:25.680 --> 00:46:26.954
Okay. I'll meet you.

406
00:46:34.000 --> 00:46:35.433
I have to meet a friend.

407
00:46:36.800 --> 00:46:38.995
That's okay.
I've got work to do at home.

408
00:46:39.360 --> 00:46:40.998
No. I don't want you to go.

409
00:46:42.160 --> 00:46:43.275
Would you please stay?

410
00:46:46.160 --> 00:46:47.388
Okay.

411
00:46:53.720 --> 00:46:54.994
<i>Fetch. boy.</i>

412
00:47:21.400 --> 00:47:24.437
<i>Now you can afford that bed</i>
<i>that lets you read. eat...</i>

413
00:47:24.800 --> 00:47:28.190
<i>... chat on the phone. watch TV. sleep</i>
<i>and relax at the touch of a button.</i>

414
00:47:28.720 --> 00:47:32.633
<i>Now you can afford soothing. gentle</i>
<i>massage. Your personal heat control.</i>

415
00:47:33.000 --> 00:47:34.194
<i>Total adjustability.</i>

416
00:47:34.560 --> 00:47:37.518
<i>At last. an adjustable bed</i>
<i>at flat bed prices.</i>

417
00:49:12.000 --> 00:49:13.194
Hello.

418
00:49:14.400 --> 00:49:15.594
Hello.

419
00:49:18.960 --> 00:49:20.188
Hello.

420
00:49:21.200 --> 00:49:23.156
<i>- Elizabeth?</i>
- Yes.

421
00:49:23.720 --> 00:49:24.755
<i>- Hi.</i>
- Hi.

422
00:49:25.120 --> 00:49:27.793
<i>Don 't talk. I have a question</i>
<i>I want to ask you.</i>

423
00:49:28.120 --> 00:49:28.996
Okay.

424
00:49:29.320 --> 00:49:33.757
<i>All the while that I was with</i>
<i>my friend. I was just wondering...</i>

425
00:49:34.720 --> 00:49:36.392
<i>... what you were doing in there.</i>

426
00:49:37.520 --> 00:49:40.796
<i>I was wondering if maybe</i>
<i>you were going through my clothes...</i>

427
00:49:41.200 --> 00:49:43.555
<i>... looking in my drawers...</i>

428
00:49:43.960 --> 00:49:46.155
<i>... looking at the things in my closet.</i>

429
00:49:47.520 --> 00:49:49.875
<i>And I said.</i>
<i>"No. she's not that kind of girl.</i>

430
00:49:50.280 --> 00:49:51.998
<i>She's a good girl. "</i>

431
00:49:52.920 --> 00:49:54.797
<i>Good girls don 't snoop. do they?</i>

432
00:49:55.200 --> 00:49:57.794
<i>So come on. you can tell me.</i>

433
00:49:58.160 --> 00:50:00.799
<i>Tell me if you've been a nosy parker.</i>

434
00:50:01.560 --> 00:50:03.676
<i>I mean. come on.</i>
<i>Really. I want to know.</i>

435
00:50:04.080 --> 00:50:06.355
<i>I'm your pal. right? So tell me.</i>

436
00:50:07.480 --> 00:50:10.153
<i>You can trust me.</i>
<i>It'll be our secret.</i>

437
00:50:11.920 --> 00:50:13.194
<i>So tell me.</i>

438
00:50:16.280 --> 00:50:17.599
<i>Tell me.</i>

439
00:50:19.160 --> 00:50:20.593
Yes.

440
00:50:22.920 --> 00:50:24.797
- Yes.
<i>- What's that?</i>

441
00:50:27.320 --> 00:50:29.993
<i>- Yes. what?</i>
- Yes. I've been a nosy parker.

442
00:50:30.560 --> 00:50:31.993
<i>Shame on you.</i>

443
00:50:33.200 --> 00:50:35.156
I didn't think you'd be here.

444
00:50:36.840 --> 00:50:37.875
Why'd you do that?

445
00:50:39.160 --> 00:50:40.593
I'm sorry.

446
00:50:43.920 --> 00:50:45.717
You've been a very bad girl.

447
00:50:46.080 --> 00:50:50.358
I want you to face the wall and raise
your skirt. because I'm gonna spank you.

448
00:50:53.920 --> 00:50:55.399
You are kidding?

449
00:50:59.200 --> 00:51:00.553
I'm not kidding.

450
00:51:04.280 --> 00:51:05.759
Oh. God.

451
00:51:17.120 --> 00:51:19.588
Who the fuck do you think you are?

452
00:52:02.520 --> 00:52:03.999
Coming.

453
00:53:29.080 --> 00:53:30.957
Your breakfast is ready.

454
00:54:15.880 --> 00:54:17.552
Will that be cash or charge?

455
00:54:19.120 --> 00:54:20.394
Cash.

456
00:54:29.080 --> 00:54:30.195
John?

457
00:54:30.560 --> 00:54:32.755
Aren't you going to ask me
how I like this?

458
00:54:35.000 --> 00:54:36.115
No.

459
00:54:53.080 --> 00:54:56.197
Did you take as good a care
of the others as you do of me?

460
00:55:01.760 --> 00:55:02.795
Did you?

461
00:55:17.560 --> 00:55:18.595
Come on. John.

462
00:55:19.000 --> 00:55:21.195
- Say. "That is gross."
- That is...

463
00:55:21.600 --> 00:55:22.999
...unacceptable.

464
00:55:45.160 --> 00:55:46.479
Just go.

465
00:56:13.200 --> 00:56:13.916
Hurry!

466
00:56:29.080 --> 00:56:30.798
Where are we going?

467
00:58:05.400 --> 00:58:06.913
I'm gonna take care of you.

468
00:58:09.999 --> 00:58:11.034
Hot soup.

469
00:58:11.439 --> 00:58:12.554
It's good.

470
00:58:20.919 --> 00:58:22.557
How did you know?

471
00:58:23.919 --> 00:58:26.558
How did you know I'd respond to you
the way I have?

472
00:58:28.159 --> 00:58:30.354
I saw myself in you.

473
00:58:51.919 --> 00:58:53.557
Do you know what. Molly?

474
00:58:57.959 --> 00:58:59.915
I can't figure this guy out.

475
00:59:04.319 --> 00:59:05.957
You know. sometimes...

476
00:59:06.319 --> 00:59:08.355
...it's so easy.

477
00:59:09.799 --> 00:59:10.993
I mean. it might be...

478
00:59:11.519 --> 00:59:13.555
...the tie they wear...

479
00:59:14.559 --> 00:59:16.754
...or the books they read.
or don't read.

480
00:59:17.159 --> 00:59:18.274
But you know.

481
00:59:18.839 --> 00:59:19.351
Know what?

482
00:59:20.479 --> 00:59:21.798
What will end it.

483
00:59:25.319 --> 00:59:27.992
So you just file it away and you wait.

484
00:59:29.119 --> 00:59:31.394
And that sort of makes it bearable.

485
00:59:34.799 --> 00:59:36.391
But with this guy...

486
00:59:39.399 --> 00:59:40.673
Maybe it's true love.

487
00:59:42.759 --> 00:59:43.987
Maybe.

488
01:01:31.639 --> 01:01:32.310
Hi.

489
01:01:34.639 --> 01:01:35.867
I brought you some lunch.

490
01:01:37.559 --> 01:01:41.757
Pastrami and oatmeal cookies.
Your favorite.

491
01:01:42.199 --> 01:01:43.552
What are you doing here?

492
01:01:44.759 --> 01:01:45.953
I was in the neighborhood...

493
01:01:46.279 --> 01:01:50.716
...and I wondered how you spent
your days without me.

494
01:01:52.439 --> 01:01:53.758
And now I know.

495
01:01:57.639 --> 01:01:59.675
Wow. you have such a big office.

496
01:02:05.919 --> 01:02:07.796
Your secretary is very attractive.

497
01:02:08.159 --> 01:02:10.627
I saw her on the way in.

498
01:02:12.719 --> 01:02:14.152
Do you always buy her lunch?

499
01:02:32.759 --> 01:02:33.953
Don't let her leave.

500
01:02:50.359 --> 01:02:51.587
I love Wall Street.

501
01:02:51.959 --> 01:02:53.756
I do. yes.

502
01:02:54.159 --> 01:02:56.514
- Why?
- I don't know.

503
01:02:57.119 --> 01:03:00.714
I love the gray flannel suits.
the shiny shoes.

504
01:03:03.159 --> 01:03:06.754
Sometimes I wonder what it
would be like to be one of the guys.

505
01:03:07.799 --> 01:03:08.470
Yeah?

506
01:03:12.159 --> 01:03:13.558
Sometimes.

507
01:03:13.879 --> 01:03:14.914
Sometimes.

508
01:03:19.359 --> 01:03:21.315
Yeah. I can understand that.

509
01:03:47.719 --> 01:03:51.109
The lady wants to know what it
would be like to be one of the boys?

510
01:03:51.839 --> 01:03:53.795
<i>The crowd is going wild!</i>

511
01:04:13.159 --> 01:04:16.356
Oh. I don't believe this.

512
01:04:30.439 --> 01:04:33.875
Don't sit down next to me looking
like that. Jesus Christ!

513
01:04:34.639 --> 01:04:36.231
- Will you take it off?
- Stop it!

514
01:04:38.079 --> 01:04:41.196
Just kidding. You look really good.
You look great.

515
01:05:07.919 --> 01:05:10.877
I'll tell you. my darling.
it's a hell of a life.

516
01:05:12.159 --> 01:05:13.877
You work and work and work.

517
01:05:14.399 --> 01:05:17.596
You meet with people that
you don't like. you don't know.

518
01:05:18.559 --> 01:05:20.595
That you don't even want to know.

519
01:05:21.719 --> 01:05:24.950
And they try to sell you things.
You try to sell them things.

520
01:05:25.759 --> 01:05:29.388
Then you go home at night. listen to
the wife nag. the kids bitch.

521
01:05:30.279 --> 01:05:32.634
You turn up the TV.
You tune everything out.

522
01:05:32.959 --> 01:05:35.712
You get up the next day
and you start over again.

523
01:05:36.919 --> 01:05:38.398
I'll tell you...

524
01:05:39.279 --> 01:05:41.998
I'll tell you. the only thing
that keeps me going...

525
01:05:43.559 --> 01:05:44.912
